# Findings and Observations



## Current Lab Status



The Wazuh single-node Docker deployment is running successfully.



### Confirmed Components



- Wazuh Dashboard is accessible from the host machine

- Wazuh API connection is online

- One Ubuntu Server agent is connected and active



---



## Environment



- Ubuntu Server VM

- VMware Workstation

- Docker-based Wazuh deployment

- Bridged networking

- GitHub repository created for documentation



---



## Confirmed Issues Encountered



During setup, the following issues were encountered and resolved:



- NAT networking prevented access from the host machine

- Bridged networking initially failed because VMware was using the wrong adapter

- VM disk space was insufficient and had to be expanded

- Docker Compose was missing and had to be installed

- Wazuh API initially appeared offline until services finished starting

- Wazuh agent initially failed because the manager IP was not configured correctly

- GitHub HTTPS push failed with 403 permi

